<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Arturo Vidal has arrived in Italy as he closes in on joining Inter Milan.</p>

<p>Vidal had a year remaining on his Barcelona contract but the Spanish club have reportedly agreed to release him for variable performance-related bonuses as opposed to the original fee of €1million (£916million).</p>

<p>As reported by Football Italia, the midfielder arrived at Linate Airport in Milan and was greeted by Inter supporters and the media. </p>

<p>Arturo Vidal has arrived in Italy as he gets set to secure his move to Serie A giants Inter Milan</p>

<p>🤳 | HEY, HOW'S IT GOING?👋 <?php echo e('@'); ?>kingarturo23 😉 pic.twitter.com/xBs9cV3FoY</p>

<p>Luis Suarez, whose own future at Barcelona is uncertain, took to Twitter to wish Vidal good luck for the next chapter in his career.</p>

<p>Suarez wrote: 'Having you as a rival was unbearable because of how great you are as a player, but having you as a partner, friend and knowing you as a person is even bigger !!!! A pleasure to have shared with a star player like you. I wish you all the best in this new stage.'</p>

<p>Vidal, who is leaving Barcelona after two years, was in good spirits as he arrived at the airport</p>

<p>Tenerte de rival era insoportable por lo grande que sos como jugador, pero tenerte de compañero, amigo y conocerte como persona sos mas grande todavía!!!! Un placer haber compartido con un crack de jugador como sos. Te deseo todo lo mejor en esta nueva etapa 👑🔝👏#crack pic.twitter.com/FdBLteAI2k</p>

<p>Vidal spent two seasons at Barcelona having joined the club from Bayern Munich in 2018. </p>

<p>During his time at Barcelona Vidal made 96 appearances and scored eleven goals.</p>

<p>Barcelona striker Luis Suarez wished Vidal good luck for the next chapter in his career</p>

<p>He won the La Liga title in the 2018-19 campaign and also won the Supercopa de Espana in 2018. </p>

<p>Inter will get their Serie A season underway next Saturday when they host Fiorentina.</p>
